'''Maura''' is a [[Hobbitish]] name probably meaning "experience, wise".<ref>{{HM|PM}} p. 50</ref>

It was the first name of [[Frodo Baggins|Maura Labingi]].
==Etymology==
The word has similarities to archaic [[Rohanese]] ''maur'' meaning "experienced". It probably comes from a [[Mannish]] root *MUR
